definition: Great Lakes/the five north American Great Lakes
big/huge/large/major/great/wide/deep/older (than)/oldest/eldest/greatly/very much/(dialect) father/father's elder or younger brother

sentences.english: These people set up a lab called the Great Lakes Environ-mental Research laboratory .
sentences.chinese: 这些人建立了一个五大湖环境调查研究实验室。

sentences.english: And ships can reach the Atlantic Ocean from the Great Lakes through the Saint Lawrence Seaway.
sentences.chinese: 而船只则能够从五大湖经过圣劳伦斯航道到达大西洋。

sentences.english: So the canal joined the Great Lakes with the Atlantic Ocean.
sentences.chinese: 所以，伊利运河就把五大湖与大西洋连接起来了。

sentences.english: Chicago sits next to Lake Michigan, one of North America's Great Lakes.
sentences.chinese: 芝加哥坐落在北美五大湖之一密歇根湖畔。

sentences.english: The great lakes along The Yangtze are also victims of the drought.
sentences.chinese: 长江流域五大湖也遭受旱灾的影响。

sentences.english: Native Americans who lived near the Great Lakes often fished by torchlight.
sentences.chinese: 居住在“五大湖”附近的土著人经常使用火把捕鱼。

sentences.english: In the Great Lakes , I hope I can sleep a lot and forget all problem.
sentences.chinese: 在五大湖，我希望我能睡得饱并忘记所有的问题。

sentences.english: But now the fish are moving north toward the Great Lakes.
sentences.chinese: 但是，现在这些鱼开始向北朝着五大湖移动。

sentences.english: Sea lampreys leave a swath of destruction as the invasive species chomps through the Great Lakes.
sentences.chinese: 七鳃鳗留下一条致命的伤口，其在五大湖大行其道。

sentences.english: It's not yet certain that Asian carp have made it into the Great Lakes.
sentences.chinese: 目前尚不确定亚洲鲤鱼已经向五大湖进军。

sentences.english: Cleveland sits next to Lake Erie, one of North America's Great Lakes.
sentences.chinese: 克利夫兰坐在旁边，北美五大湖之一的伊利湖。

sentences.english: 'I really want to see those lakes, ' Linda says.
sentences.chinese: 何丽英说，我真的很想看看五大湖。

sentences.english: It was released to coincide with the first-ever "Great Lakes Week" event, which is bringing together U.
sentences.chinese: 这份报告是配合首届“五大湖周”宣传活动而发布的。
